<br>
That pet taking 50% of the exp is rubbish too. Grant it that if they removed it, it would make charm kiting extremely easy but it really screws me up when soloing/duoing. Soloing, I can probably out damage my pet but it takes a lot of mana and forces me to med for a long time (hopes for bob from velks one day =D). But in duoing, it is very hard to kos the pet. Take for instance, I was duoing with queegg awhile back and to make it worthwhile, we would have to pull at least double the amount of mobs I would need to when soloing. Well, I couldn't keep nuking to deal 50% of the damage in a lot of those pulls and the pet took a huge amount of the exp (33% to be exact) and that is crap...<br>
<br>
Not to forget that 14 items with the same ability of reclaim energy is a lot. I wish they would upgrade a lot of the mage items too. I don't even use a lot of the effects that come with the items. The only ss armor piece I use rarely are the boots to summon bandages (Robe one is useless and I haven't used it since pre 56 and legs give me burnout 3 when I have bo 4).<br>
<br>
The real part that scares me is that Alan said that Frenzied Burnout is working. I consider FB the equivalent of manaburn, dire charm, divine something that paladins get that allows em to get high crits on undead mobs, etc. Well mages with the skill say that it isn't too much better then a regular pet, just misses a lot more, and the big kamakaze ae attack the pet does just makes it so the pet kills itself. Plus, FB only adds about 5 or so dps to the pet and only lasting for 36 seconds, it doesn't really help much...<br>
<br>
I guess this post was more of rant than anything else but it is good to get stuff like this off your chest =D. There is a ton of stuff I left out but you can figure out what they are. Oh, and if you have no idea what i'm talking about, Absor replied to a huge list of mage Q's today and although it was nice, it was kind of depressing also. Not too forget that he didn't answer a lot of the important questions too.<br>
